WEBVTT

00:04.710 --> 00:10.011
normally i wouldn't waste my time meeting with
a college freshman groveling for an internship.

00:10.032 --> 00:11.415
well, thank you, miss kahn.

00:11.451 --> 00:12.355
bitterman !

00:12.857 --> 00:13.562
yeah, chief ?

00:13.597 --> 00:15.455
where's that piece on senator jennings ?

00:15.487 --> 00:16.802
i- i-i'm
typing it up.

00:16.826 --> 00:18.247
i don't see your fingers moving.

00:18.287 --> 00:21.422
20 minutes, or they'll be
twiddling over the want ads.

00:21.622 --> 00:22.735
of course, chief.

00:23.627 --> 00:24.649
where was i ?

00:24.684 --> 00:25.717
the internship.

00:25.753 --> 00:27.890
oh, right, right,
right. you didn't get it.

00:27.937 --> 00:28.559
what ?

00:30.071 --> 00:31.011
well, then...

00:31.328 --> 00:32.267
why am i here ?

00:32.290 --> 00:35.484
curiosity. it's the backbone
of any decent reporter.

00:35.520 --> 00:37.551
have you got backbone, sullivan ?

00:37.586 --> 00:38.368
yeah, i...

00:39.060 --> 00:42.442
you had a column here a couple
of years ago, didn't you ?

00:42.642 --> 00:43.980
when i was in high school.

00:44.203 --> 00:46.728
well, that is quite an accomplishment

00:46.944 --> 00:50.561
to have your own by-line when
you're practically still in diapers.

00:50.811 --> 00:54.111
i mean, a lot of reporters...
well, real reporters

00:54.157 --> 00:57.105
work for years struggling before
they can get that kind of a chance.

00:57.128 --> 00:59.970
i just wanted to meet the
kid that could pull that off.

01:00.178 --> 01:00.871
thanks.

01:01.024 --> 01:04.382
oh, well, don't thank
me. thank lionel luthor.

01:04.415 --> 01:10.826
he's the one who arm-twisted the old chief editor
into dropping your juvenile pablum into this paper.

01:11.436 --> 01:13.162
i didn't ask lionel to do that.

01:13.198 --> 01:15.567
well, you didn't say
"no" either, did you ?

01:15.861 --> 01:20.264
then you must have done something to
piss lionel off because he got you fired.

01:20.663 --> 01:22.389
i remember that day.

01:22.422 --> 01:23.878
i believe we had cake.

01:25.968 --> 01:29.737
miss kahn, i don't expect to be
given a column like last time.

01:30.759 --> 01:35.350
i'm willing to start from the bottom and work
my way up without any help or arm-twisting.

01:35.385 --> 01:37.839
all i want is the
opportunity to prove myself.

01:37.874 --> 01:39.800
being a part of this world,

01:39.976 --> 01:42.028
working at the daily planet, it's...

01:42.275 --> 01:43.954
it's always been my dream.

01:43.978 --> 01:46.831
well, we all have to wake up
sometime, don't we, sullivan ?

01:47.066 --> 01:49.565
by the way, we don't validate.

01:56.645 --> 01:58.310
you know what, miss kahn ?

01:59.649 --> 02:04.134
i know you may be editor in chief now,
but even you had to start somewhere,

02:04.193 --> 02:08.078
and i am not going to give up
until i get the same chance.

02:16.826 --> 02:19.442
i started by being a damn good reporter.

02:19.876 --> 02:21.004
you want a break ?

02:22.800 --> 02:24.057
bring me a story.

02:26.111 --> 02:31.064
<i>okay, let's stop for a second. in case you
can't tell, i was completely freaked out.</i>

02:31.275 --> 02:33.447
<i>pauline kahn had thrown
down the gauntlet.</i>

02:33.482 --> 02:36.970
<i>the woman had two pulitzers. i
had a high-school service plaque</i>

02:37.006 --> 02:40.082
<i>and absolutely no idea where my
big story was going to come from.</i>

02:40.399 --> 02:44.978
<i>little did i know that 10 city blocks
away, it was about to bite me in the ass...</i>

02:45.096 --> 02:47.985
<i>well, more like the neck,
but we'll get to that later.</i>

02:48.032 --> 02:50.791
<i>welcome to the tri-psi sorority house.</i>

02:50.932 --> 02:53.891
<i>i think that's greek for
"bimbos, bikinis, and beer."</i>

02:56.366 --> 02:59.607
pizza pizza, delivered
in 28 minutes, piping...

03:01.662 --> 03:02.472
...hot.

03:02.531 --> 03:05.912
oh, my god, we are so starving.

03:07.417 --> 03:09.484
mmm, let's eat in the jacuzzi.

